iter).hasToString(\"Hello Velocity\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadDirectiveRejectsClassesThatDoNotImplementDirective() {\n        RuntimeInstance runtime = configuredRuntimeInstance();\n\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> runtime.loadDirective(String.class.getName()))\n                .isInstanceOf(VelocityException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"does not implement\")\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"Directive\");\n    }\n\n    private static RuntimeInstance configuredRuntimeInstance() {\n        RuntimeInstance runtime = new RuntimeInstance();\n        runtime.setProperty(\"runtime.log.logsystem.class\", NullLogChute.class.getName());\n        runtime.setProperty(\"resource.manager.class\", ResourceManagerImpl.class.getName());\n        runtime.setProperty(\"resource.manager.cache.class\", ResourceCacheImpl.class.getName());\n        runtime.setProperty(\"parser.pool.class\", ParserPoolImpl.class.getName());\n        runtime.setProperty(\"runtime.introspector.uberspect\", UberspectImpl.class.getName());\n        runtime.setProperty(\"file.resource.loader.class\", FileResourceLoader.class.getName());\n        return runtime;\n    }\n}\n"}
