[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating parser initialization**\n\nI'm considering that other tests might affect the parser pool. However, if a static field was set by a previous test, it doesn't call the class$ for a message unless the field is non-null. I’m wondering if earlier tests might have covered the class$ in RuntimeInstance before it gets reported as uncovered. Could it also be that the static field was initialized during a native image build? Hmm, that's an interesting thought.\n\n**Investigating class$ coverage issue**\n\nI'm looking into a problem where the class$ coverage only shows one method line, despite many locations invoking it. The dynamic-access report points to a call site inside the class$ method, and I wonder if it’s being called properly. There might be a bug in the initializeSpecificEventHandler. Also, it's puzzling if a second execution under native isn't happening despite the report suggesting used resources. I'm also considering if Class.forName is called, but does it get missed if the class name is already known?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08bf52b2da2a0476016a23b675a1288195af8516d239f67ed7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqI7aD76RbuejboddG_mJTxhrEB7BApqs59LQRU_eKclJK4A5Fl7OdU9LH8Lqulpusl47z4SPDyn069y5fV-Tr_X_7RTgFgQdyFSEfK45oyQUZeTi3j0r3Ub4ryGpVSZjsFITJhMEYrSrF2DaRCG5DVFqz2c-BDZtnSZpfPeMq55yDFAiB9gLms8a7mU9nNUVjyQ0tG8GeydM0W6ulFg0ZQu_cUiy28jyqMhdINpZ7_O3or1rhGao9bdxY9nFYsK8B6VZ9e2hAjy4sIwcBefoGH1kFIuI1JmAyItu0CIC7u1S4OuyibHsktldk2Jy_aQp9hFEVN_zBU1vD-QRmEgsYsm6gVR77QI8wIFegdln_7iST_74zIDYO0JrfU3eYsS1tK4-m8C2OuxJChtmdXBSnqs7qjKRX13mcOlXaozr3UZBmbMGp1wobmWtSiDE9ei5UZhGyqu5rvKRzYEwLcGFn6NgAe_PFCPW-PV1WL_C2PBuAFSyyaKmn-tICuCS3c_2kSP8rUIvXnfLsol5qgVoZfx_cc5lKzxn_l0PTQ6hRVZsJXhcfjB-JewFux32b_9o1c3Il2leSji1ziiOFnT_tyNDx-j8sUgqhhU9jt8MHHlxczpYm79IM7JiI7dMSbxTmXiKYA2XhjSureLOwb0VssNkwr_khabmtdGs8FmvHcH1wlfPG6JOWITBqq